By January 2004, that plan would replace units currently in Iraq with a lesser number of units, according to a briefing presented to the Congress by General Jack Keane, Acting Chief of Staff of the Army, on July 23, 2003.
That conclusion is based on the additional assumption that DoD would not send units to Iraq that had returned from occupation duty to their home station within the past year.
